Ask HN: OpenAI services are blocked in Cambodia, how to circumvent that?
text:
I'm traveling in Cambodia and got to know that I can't access my OpenAI account in this country. I want to build a product using GPT3.5 turbo API but for that I need to access OpenAI account. This is the error I see when I visit https://platform.openai.com/: "OpenAI's services are not available in your country. (error=unsupported_country)"

How to circumvent that? Any recommendations for privacy-friendly VPN or any other solution?

PS: I use Chrome on Mac.

title: Ask HN: What to Do with a Gifted Laptop?
text:
I will be gifted a used 2019 x86-laptop. While I will eventually give it away to someone in need, what could I do with it in the meantime? This excludes modifying the hardware or buying extra hardware.

My ideas so far:

* install Linux from scratch

* install Android (e.g. Bliss OS)

* make it a typewriter with a very small Linux distro running Emacs Window Manager and "only" provide Emacs for text production

* boots directly into a C64 emulator to relive my childhood

Further, more creative ideas, guys and gals?

text:
I've worked with Python in the past but never went deep enough to compare the typecheckers. There are several: Pyre, Pyright, Mypy, Pytype.

It's unclear which is the best choice. I'd love to hear the take of a seasoned Python developer.

title: Ask HN: What are you building with the current wave of AI and LLMs?
text:
With the recent advancements in AI and large language models (LLMs) like GPT-4, I'm curious to learn what kind of projects you all have been working on utilizing these powerful tools.

It's clear that we're in the midst of a transformative period for AI, and the possibilities for its applications seem endless.

Personally, I've been experimenting with GPT-4 to create a platform that generates content for niche blogs, which has shown promising results so far. The ability of LLMs to understand context and generate relevant, high-quality content has made the process of content creation far more efficient.

Here are a few areas I've seen people leveraging AI and LLMs:

1. Personalized learning platforms: Utilizing AI to create tailored educational content for students based on their strengths and weaknesses.

2. Sentiment analysis: Companies analyzing customer reviews and social media posts to better understand their audience and improve their products and services.

3. Content summarization: Summarizing long articles and documents into concise summaries for easier consumption.

4. Creative writing and storytelling: Assisting authors and screenwriters in generating ideas, characters, and plots for their stories.

5. Medical diagnosis: Enhancing the diagnostic process by analyzing vast amounts of medical data and generating relevant insights for doctors.

These are just a few examples, and I'm sure there are many more interesting projects out there. So, please share your experiences and ideas!

* What projects are you currently working on or have completed that incorporate AI and LLMs?

* What challenges have you faced while working with these technologies?

* How do you think the landscape of AI and LLMs will evolve in the next few years?

Looking forward to hearing your thoughts and learning from your experiences!
